<seg id=1> The US Open going to the third day </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> Beijing, Sep. 1 (Xinhua News Agency) As foreign news agencies reported, the US Open went into the third day on Auguest 31. Champion of last US Open, Pete Sampras cured from his pains, easily defeated his rival by 3:0, and entered the second round. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> The number one seed currently, American player, Sampras has not turned up sine mid July. His return after recovering from injury showed pretty good sport state. He easily beat the South African player in 3 games, all scored as 6:2, within one hour and a half, and entered the second round. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The No. 8 seed, Ukrainian An Medvidev also defeated his opponent by 6:3, 6:4 and 6:0,entering the second round as well. </seg>
<seg id=5> His success was just on time for serving as the present for his 20th birthday. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> In the women's games, the No. 2 seed, Spainish Sanchez was boldly challenged from her French rival N. Tauziat, but Sanchez finally win by 6:2 and 7:6, entering the third round. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> The fifth seed, Date Kimiko, from Japan, the ninth, M. Fernandez of the US and the 1990 champion Savatini from Argentina all smoothly got into the third round. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=8> The most recent news is that, US player Micheal Chang beat his opponent in the second round by 4:6, 6:2, 6:3 and 7:6, and entered the third round. </seg>
</p>
